Fresh Produce Retail Analytics Report

Executive Summary
Analysis of 800K+ transactions from July 2020 to December 2023 revealed three key areas for profit recovery: pricing strategy, waste management, and operational efficiency.

Key Findings & Tactical Recommendations
•	Profitability vs. Waste Exposure: The business generates $3.37M in revenue and delivers $1.03M in net profit a healthy 30.68% profit margin. However, $209.95K was lost due to the spoilage of 46.61K units. Analysis revealed that existing discounting strategies fail to clear aging stock which erode potential profit. Strategic interventions across pricing, waste management, and operational timing offer significant margin recovery.
•	Spoilage Concentration: A targeted audit reveals that 3 top items account for 23% of all spoiled inventory. We recommend reducing order volumes for these 3 high loss items and reallocating capital into lower risk produce categories.
•	Seasonal Waste Spikes: Seasonal trends show that summer peak months (July to August) and winter transitions (December to January) experience 60% higher spoilage than spring and early summer. I recommend cutting purchase orders by 25% to 30% during these volatile periods and running clearance promotions one month prior to historical peak spoilage windows.
•	Peak Traffic Windows: Customer shopping behavior concentrates heavily between 9:00 AM to 11:00 AM and 3:00 PM to 7:00 PM. Operations should optimize shift schedules to increase floor coverage and complete shelf restocking immediately before these high intensity hours.
•	Dynamic & Age Based Pricing Strategy: Correlation analysis indicates that high loss items are rarely discounted, proving that discounts are not being leveraged to mitigate spoilage risk. We recommend implementing an Age Based Discount Matrix:
o	1 to 4 Days on Shelf: Full Retail Price (100%)
o	5 to 6 Days on Shelf: 15% Discount
o	7+ Days on Shelf: 35% Discount or Clearance

Action Plan Summary
1.	Implement Age Based & Volatility Pricing: Automate price markdowns based on shelf life and wholesale price variance.
2.	Mitigate Top 3 Spoilage Items: Re evaluate order quantities and supplier terms for Xixia Mushroom, Broccoli, and Yunnan Shengcai.
3.	Optimize Hourly Staffing: Align labor allocation with peak store traffic windows (9:00 AM to 11:00 AM and 3:00 PM to 7:00 PM).
4.	Smooth Seasonal Spoilage Peaks: Reduce purchase volumes by 25% to 30% heading into August and January.
These recommendations could unlock $600K-800K in additional annual profit with minimal implementation cost.

